### Marine Corps Air Station New River

Marine Corps Air Station New River (MCAS New River), identified by [ICAO airport code](/International_Civil_Aviation_Organization_airport_code) KNCA and [FAA LID](/Location_identifier) NCA, is a pivotal United States Marine Corps installation situated near [Jacksonville, North Carolina](/Jacksonville,_North_Carolina), in the eastern expanse of the state. This air station is primarily dedicated to helicopter and tilt-rotor operations, playing a crucial role in the projection of [United States Marine Corps](/United_States_Marine_Corps) power. In 1972, the airfield itself was bestowed the honor of being named McCutcheon Field, a tribute to General [Keith B. McCutcheon](/Keith_B._McCutcheon), an individual widely recognized as one of the foundational figures in the evolution of Marine Corps helicopter aviation. The strategic proximity of MCAS New River to [Marine Corps Base Camp Lejeune](/Marine_Corps_Base_Camp_Lejeune) allows for the sharing of certain facilities, notably with [Camp Geiger](/Camp_Geiger), fostering a degree of operational synergy.

